{
  "name": "Dust of Dryness",
  "type": "consumable",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>This small packet contains 1d6 + 4 pinches of dust. You can use an action to sprinkle a pinch of it over water. The dust turns a &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} of water 15 feet on a side into one marble-sized pellet, which floats or rests near where the dust was sprinkled. The pellet's weight is negligible.</p>\n<p>Someone can use an action to smash the pellet against a hard surface, causing the pellet to shatter and release the water the dust absorbed. Doing so ends that pellet's magic.</p>\n<p>An &amp;Reference[elemental]{elemental} composed mostly of water that is exposed to a pinch of the dust must make a [[/save con 13 format=long]], taking 10d6 &amp;Reference[necrotic]{necrotic} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n</div>",
